<doc id="487060" wikidata="Q4862485" url="?curid=487060" title="Baron Hives">
<text>Baron Hives, of Duffield in the County of Derby, is a title in the Peerage of the United Kingdom. It was created 7 July 1950 for the Ernest Hives, Chairman of Rolls-Royce Ltd. the title is held by his grandson, the third Baron, who succeeded his uncle in 1997.

==Baron Hives (1950)==
*Ernest Walter Hives, 1st Baron Hives (1886–1965)
*John Warwick Hives, 2nd Baron Hives (1913–1997)
*Matthew Peter Hives, 3rd Baron Hives (b. 1971)

The heir apparent is the present holder&#x27;s son, the Hon. Henry Peter David Hives (born 2024).

