<doc id="487061" wikidata="Q132634" url="?curid=487061" title="Vigna">
<text>Vigna is a genus of plants in the legume family, Fabaceae, with a pantropical distribution. It includes some well-known cultivated species, including many types of beans. Some are former members of the genus &quot;Phaseolus&quot;. According to &quot;Hortus Third&quot;, &quot;Vigna&quot; differs from &quot;Phaseolus&quot; in biochemistry and pollen structure, and in details of the style and stipules.

&quot;Vigna&quot; is also commonly confused with the genus &quot;Dolichos&quot;, but the two differ in stigma structure.

&quot;Vigna&quot; are herbs or occasionally subshrubs. The leaves are pinnate, divided into 3 leaflets. The inflorescence is a raceme of yellow, blue, or purple pea flowers. The fruit is a legume pod of varying shapes containing seeds.

Familiar food species include the adzuki bean (&quot;V. angularis&quot;), the black gram (&quot;V. mungo&quot;), the cowpea (&quot;V. unguiculata&quot;, including the variety known as the black-eyed pea), and the mung bean (&quot;V. radiata&quot;). Each of these may be used as a whole bean, a bean paste, or as bean sprouts.

The genus is named after Domenico Vigna, a seventeenth-century Italian botanist and director of the Orto botanico di Pisa.

==Uses==
Root tubers of &quot;Vigna&quot; species have traditionally been used as food by the Indigenous Peoples of the Northern Territory.

==Selected species==
The genus &quot;Vigna&quot; contains at least 90 species, including:
===Subgenus &quot;Ceratotropis&quot;===
*&quot;Vigna aconitifolia&quot; —moth bean, mat bean, Turkish gram
*&quot;Vigna angularis&quot; —adzuki bean, red bean
**&quot;Vigna angularis&quot; var. &quot;angularis&quot; 
**&quot;Vigna angularis&quot; var. &quot;nipponensis&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna glabrescens&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna grandiflora&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna hirtella&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna minima&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna mungo&quot; —black gram, black lentil, white lentil, urd-bean, urad bean
**&quot;Vigna mungo&quot; var. &quot;silvestris&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna nakashimae&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna nepalensis&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna radiata&quot; —mung bean, green gram, golden gram, mash bean, green soy, celera-bean, Jerusalem-pea
**&quot;Vigna radiata&quot; var. &quot;radiata&quot; 
**&quot;Vigna radiata&quot; var. &quot;sublobata&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna reflexopilosa&quot; —Creole-bean
**&quot;Vigna reflexopilosa&quot; var. &quot;reflexopilosa&quot; 
**&quot;Vigna reflexopilosa&quot; var. &quot;glabra&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna riukiuensis&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna stipulacea&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna subramaniana&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna tenuicaulis&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna trilobata&quot; —jungle mat bean, jungli-bean, African gram, three-lobe-leaved cowpea
*&quot;Vigna trinervia&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna umbellata&quot; —ricebean, red bean, climbing mountain-bean, mambi bean, Oriental-bean

===Subgenus &quot;Haydonia&quot;===
*&quot;Vigna monophylla&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna nigritia&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna schimperi&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna triphylla&quot; 

===Subgenus &quot;Lasiospron&quot;===
*&quot;Vigna diffusa&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna juruana&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna lasiocarpa&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna longifolia&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna schottii&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna trichocarpa&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna vexillata&quot; —zombi pea, wild cowpea
**&quot;Vigna vexillata var. angustifolia&quot;
**&quot;Vigna vexillata&quot; var. &quot;youngiana&quot;

===Subgenus &quot;Vigna&quot;===
*&quot;Vigna ambacensis&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna angivensis&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna filicaulis&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna friesiorum&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna gazensis&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna hosei&quot; —Sarowak/Sarawak bean
*&quot;Vigna luteola&quot; —Dalrymple vigna
*&quot;Vigna membranacea&quot; 
**&quot;Vigna membranacea&quot; subsp. &quot;caesia&quot; 
**&quot;Vigna membranacea&quot; subsp. &quot;membranacea&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna monantha&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna racemosa&quot; 
*&quot;Vigna subterranea&quot; —Bambara groundnut, Congo goober, hog-peanut, jugo bean, &quot;njugumawe&quot; (Swahili) (sometimes separated in &quot;Voandzeia&quot;)
*&quot;Vigna unguiculata&quot; —cowpea, crowder pea, Southern pea, Reeve&#x27;s-pea, snake-bean
**&quot;Vigna unguiculata&quot; subsp. &quot;cylindrica&quot;—catjang
**&quot;Vigna unguiculata&quot; subsp. &quot;dekindtiana&quot;—wild cowpea, African cowpea, Ethiopian cowpea
**&quot;Vigna unguiculata&quot; subsp. &quot;sesquipedalis&quot;—yardlong bean, long-podded cowpea, asparagus bean, Chinese long bean, pea-bean
**&quot;Vigna unguiculata&quot; subsp. &quot;unguiculata&quot;—black-eyed pea, black-eyed bean

